  "prompt": "How can I prepare for NDA exam?",
  "response": "To prepare for the NDA (National Defence Academy) exam, follow these steps:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Written exam: Mathematics and General Ability Test (GAT)\n- Interview/SSB (Services Selection Board)\n\n2. Study Materials\n- NCERT textbooks\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Recommended guidebooks\n- Online study resources\n\n3. Mathematics Preparation\n- Cover algebra, trigonometry, geometry\n- Practice problem-solving\n- Focus on quick calculation techniques\n- Solve mock tests\n\n4. General Ability Test Preparation\n- English language skills\n- General knowledge\n- Current affairs\n- Basic science\n- History and geography\n- Reasoning and logical thinking\n\n5. Physical Fitness\n- Regular exercise\n- Focus on stamina and strength\n- Practice running, push-ups, sit-ups\n- Maintain good physical health\n\n6. Recommended Study Strategy\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Practice daily\n- Take mock tests\n- Time management\n- Solve previous years' papers\n\n7. Additional Preparation\n- Read newspapers\n- Watch current affairs programs\n- Join coaching classes if possible\n- Develop communication skills\n\n8. Mental Preparation\n- Stay motivated\n- Practice meditation\n- Build confidence\n- Develop leadership qualities\n\nConsistent preparation and a systematic approach are key to cracking the NDA exam.",
